data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
MK64Help tool by DeadHamster <3Hamp
Copy will copy all files from the first directory selected, to the next directory selected, based on the search string. Try using things like
*.c *.sgi *.h
It will also search ALL subdirectories, so be cautious which folder you select.
The Compress/Expand options will compress and decompress the data listed on the button. Segment 7 is the special F3DEX bytecode that Mario Kart 64 uses, where full F3DEX is compressed using assumed parameters and a limited function-set.
Batch .C Texture -> PNG will attempt to convert a directory of .C files that have texture data as byte arrays into .PNG images. This will only work on compressed images, such as those in the Kimura archive in the folder "image" .
Segment 4 -> TXT will take an UNINFLATED vert cache and export it to a .TXT file.
Inflate Vert Cache will add data to the vert cache to match it's size in RAM. This can be done to properly find data by offset in the Vert Cache data.
Level Geometry -> TXT will take an UNINFLATED Segment 4 and Segment 7 file and export a text file that lists each triangle's positions, with seperators for each object listing the offset in the data where the object's draw commands end.
